natural problem: Evaluate $\log_3 27\sqrt3$. Express your answer as an improper fraction.

a_0.formal problem:
theorem
fixes log_3 :: "real \<Rightarrow> real"
assumes h0 : "log_3 = (\<lambda>x. ln x / ln 3)"
and h1 : "\<forall>x. log_3 (3 powr x) = x"
shows  "log_3 (27 * sqrt 3) = 7 / 2"
a_0.formal solution:
(* ### Problem
 Evaluate $\log_3 27\sqrt3$. Express your answer as an improper fraction. The final Answer is \frac72
 ### Proof
 We have $ 27\sqrt3 = (3^3)(3^\frac12)=3^{(3+\frac12)}=3^{\frac72}$.
 Therefore, $\log_3 27\sqrt3=\boxed{\frac72}$.
 *)

theorem
fixes log_3 :: "real \<Rightarrow> real"
assumes h0 : "log_3 = (\<lambda>x. ln x / ln 3)"
and h1 : "\<forall>x. log_3 (3 powr x) = x"
shows  "log_3 (27 * sqrt 3) = 7 / 2"
 proof- 
  show ?thesis sledgehammer
